We would like to find a candidate that is looking to develop their skills and seeks growth opportunities within the company.   In return, we will provide on-the-job training and support, challenging new tasks and exposure to new technology.Infomedia is the global leader in automotive software, providing SaaS solutions from our large suite of products in pursuit of creating efficiencies and process improvements for our clients. Our team gets to build, implement and support some of the coolest products on the market, using the latest tech in an environment where ideas are nurtured, curiosity is rewarded, and collaboration is key to our success. We are evolving quickly and so we are on the lookout for those who thrive in fast paced and ever-changing environments where innovation and continual improvement are the norm. You know, the people who are forever curious, asking questions and seeking answers, challenging prevailing perceptions in pursuit of the best outcomes and not the "normal" outcomes. Our team are not leaders in our industry by accident, we are forever challenging each other to be better in a supportive culture conducive with high performance, creativity and achievement. We challenge you to challenge us.
We offer:
Quarterly meetups
Relaxed and informal but very high performing culture
Social events
What will the role look like on a day to day basis?
Many of Nidasu's products receive data from multiple sources; the data is standardized and used in our applications to create key performance reports.
We would like someone to join our team to generally assist with tasks such as:
Adding data from our clients into Nidasu products;
Managing and reviewing data we receive from Dealers;
Regularly source data from Automotive Distributors, update Nidasu applications, and check the data quality;
Comparing reports from Nidasu's applications with reports from other sources; report on inconsistencies;
Reviewing data matching processes; discover trends and reporting findings;
Assisting with the support requests raised by our clients.
Experience and attributes that will translate into success: 
Please be comfortable with using Microsoft Excel;
Have very keen attention to detail;
Have good written and verbal communication skills;
Be flexible and adaptable;
Be happy to work in a team.

#Closer #Braver #Faster

Workforce Data & Insights, People and Culture
Full time Permanent Opportunity
Sydney or Melbourne

The Role
We have an exciting NEW opportunity that has come available for Manager, Workforce Data & Insight to join IAG's Workforce Futures & Analytics team on a permanent full-time basis. By investing and improving our analytics capabilities, you and your colleagues/team will influence and inform the IAG and People & Culture strategy and its execution through those insights. In this role you will manage and improve the content, form and production of workforce insights and analytics enabling IAG with the essential information it needs for workforce management and governance. You will also determine the requirements of IAG's workforce data priorities to continually enhance insights and enable IAG to better leverage people analytics across the employee life cycle.
The successful candidate will have proven agility as you effectively collaborate and influence, providing data driven analysis to achieve tangible objectives. You will showcase your proven expertise determining and overseeing the manner with which workforce analytics projects are managed ensuring rigorous statistical and hypothesis testing methodologies are utilised.  
A key challenge will be your ability to provide strategic leadership as you identify, recommend and manage the types and forms of core workforce and people data that IAG needs to better leverage people analytics in a sustainable way.
Key Responsibilities

Review, determine and produce the framework of core workforce insights needed by IAG to drive organisational performance and mitigate risk;
Develop and continually improve the way workforce and people insights are generated, leveraging contemporary data and analytical methods, tools and automation solutions;
Determine and ensure the appropriate standards and management of core workforce data to produce workforce insights,
Ensure that internal and external service providers of workforce data, data management, workforce information and systems know the standards and deliverables they need to meet;
To ensure effective insights, reports and recommendations are developed for the governance of organisational design as its relates to job architecture, Leading@IAG, structure, job design, workflows and capability;
To continually review and improve IAG's job architecture to ensure that it is fit for purpose;
Develop plans and initiatives that supports P&C's data informed decision-making capability.

Skills & Experience

5+ years' experience managing human resources reporting, analytics, and data roles and/or overseeing an overall system of data management, business reporting and analysis; 
Demonstrated experience turning complex data in to information for business decision making;
Experience leveraging Microsoft Excel or other data manipulation tools, including reporting and analytics tools;
Advanced skills building dashboards and utilising data visualisation tools like Tableau and Power BI;
Understand how to interrogate data bases using programming languages like SQL;
Understanding of Agile Project methodology and change management approaches;
Experience managing and leading work in complex matrix based organisations;
Tertiary qualification in relevant fields including Business, Statistics or Information Technology;

About Us
At IAG, we believe that everyone has a unique point of view to share, shaped by their life experiences, cultures & passions. We celebrate and commit to:
#Proud to be me - we value difference, not sameness
#Together - harnessing our collective wisdom enables us to be our best for our customers & each other
#No boxes - it's not about labels, boxes or categories. It's about building a diverse and inclusive mindset into everything we do
IAG is the largest general insurance group in Australia and New Zealand. IAG owns some of the region's most trusted brands, including NRMA Insurance, CGU, SGIO
How to Apply
Start your career journey with us and click ‘Apply'!
In addition to a diverse and inclusive culture, some of our benefits include 13% superannuation, 50% insurance discounts, flexible work and leave options, generous parental leave and return to work program, recognition and reward program, and various corporate partner discounts.
We encourage Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders to apply for this position.
Contact Email: Heidi.Ruchotzke@iag.com.au  or Phone: 02 9292 3349 for a confidential discussion.

MinterEllison people aspire to be our clients best partner. Collaboration, innovation and opportunity are the foundation of our workplace environment. We welcome people who want exciting careers in high performing teams.
Purpose of the role
The Business Analyst will contribute to the effective delivery of high quality projects and work packages for operational and improvement projects, and build upon a body of knowledge of complex transactional systems (preferably finance related), to manage business requirements, analysis and design outputs.
Job description
Working as part of a tight-knit, high performing team, the Business Analyst will become a resident expert with in depth product expertise and ability to leverage excellent Business Analysis skills to effectively participate in projects and software design and delivery.
Responsibilities include:

Participate in requirements gathering workshops and other forums;
Document user stories / requirements, seek feedback from multiple parties and update as required;
Collaborate to complete full requirements analysis, including functional, data, security and stakeholder impact analysis;
Build deep financial systems product expertise;
Co-ordinate meetings, agendas, minutes and action lists;
Liaise with developers, SMEs and project team members on work items associated with project deliverables;
Assist with test planning to fulfil the business requirements and review test cases to ensure adequate coverage;
Maintain issues registers, defect logs, run sheets and other project artefacts as required;
Contribute to continuous improvement of business analysis processes, activities and outputs, with a focus on agility, responsiveness and high quality outcomes;
Carry out other business analyst tasks as requested by the Business Analysis Team Leader or Head of Business Systems;
Availability for go live testing outside work hours.

More about you
On your first day, we expect you to have:

Product expertise in complex Finance / ERP systems;
Demonstrable experience analysing requirements/user stories and developing specifications with a focus on robust, scalable solutions;
The ability to quickly learn key modules and functions of a system, and understand key system tables and relationships;
The ability to demonstrate a strong understanding of the commercial environment and the key drivers of the business and to be flexible in meeting changing requirements and priorities;
Experience as a team member on either small or large projects, including estimation of own work deliverables and collaboration with other team members;
Ability to assist with and review test cases as per requirements and execute some testing as required by the Test Manager;
Beginner to intermediate SQL knowledge;
Good Understanding of and strong adherence to ITIL principles;
Exposure ideally to both waterfall and agile methodologies;
A sound understanding of project delivery and your role in the software development life cycle;
A good communicator, excellent at building relationships and communicating promptly re issues and blockers; 
Presents new ideas, seeks and develops suggestions;
Maintains a pro-active, flexible and collaborative attitude.

Bonus points for someone who has:

Experience with Legal Practice Management systems;
2 - 3 years' experience in professional services or comparable environment

Who we are
We embrace flexibility and empower all our people to learn, grow and become truly extraordinary. We provide our future leaders with best practice learning and development programs to accelerate and grow their careers. We value diversity in the workplace and care about ensuring you balance your professional goals with your commitments and interests outside of work. We have a wide range of social, financial and health benefits to support your wellbeing.
How to apply
We prefer to deal with you directly, so please follow the prompts below to apply.  For specific queries about this opportunity please contact Alyce Bennett on Alyce.Bennett@minterellison.com. 
MinterEllison does not accept agency submissions unless approval to do so has been given by a member of the Resourcing Team. Approved agency submissions must be submitted through our on-line system. Candidates submitted directly to any employee or Partner of the firm will not be considered valid and will not be considered by MinterEllison. MinterEllison will not be liable for a recruitment fee in these circumstances.
To be eligible to apply for this role you must be legally permitted to work in Australia.

At NAB, we believe success comes from our people. We're committed to supporting your talent and skills through your career, as you help us build a culture that affects change for our customers - and for the community too.
The Opportunity
Our Digital Forms team is seeking an experienced Technical Business Analyst who is a passionate, results-focused individual to take accountability for delivering quality requirements in Agile environment within our digital forms space.
The successful candidate will be responsible for working within agile scrum teams to analyse, collaborate and document business and technical requirements required to support our build team. This will be done using an iterative approach enabling the team to build and ship our business priorities whilst employing agile delivery methodologies to ensure consistent, accurate and timely outcomes.
As the role is technical in nature, it is important that the successful candidate has a firm grasp of development principles.  Knowledge and experience working with any formal programming languages will be beneficial for this role.
Primary responsibilities will include:

Work with business users to elicit and define user requirements using the most appropriate method(s), and translate them into functional requirements, and contribute to the management of client expectations;
Assist in the technical breakdown of solutions and contribute to high level solutioning of new initiatives;
Analysis and specification of requirements that are uniquely traceable, verifiable and prioritised in a manner that is acceptable to both business and technology stakeholders;
Effective use of data and process modelling tools (including, but not limited to process mapping, business, object and dataflow modelling) to analyse and represent information in an effective form in order to translate business requirements into meaningful statements of work;
Assess existing processes to identify redesign or enhancement opportunities to deliver improved productivity or efficiency to the business;
Assist and lead continuous improvement initiatives across the platform, driving agile best practice and simplification in the way we do things;
Driving opportunities for improving solutions through monitoring, analysis and ownership of features in production.

The successful applicant will have the following skills and experience: 

At least 2 – 3 years of experience as a Technical Business Analyst;
Experience in a feature driven delivery environment utilising agile delivery techniques as well as engaging and influencing stakeholders;
Strong experience in business and process analysis, mapping and engineering;
Experience working in large, complex projects in an unpredictable environment with competing priorities;
Firm grasp of development principle;
Excellent communication, organisation and time management skills;
Knowledge and experience working with any formal programming languages will be beneficial.  

In return we offer a rewarding work environment, structured training, on-going career progression, hack days and personal development in a supportive team environment.
To be eligible to apply, you must be an Australian / New Zealand citizen or hold permanent residency status in Australia.
We embrace diversity of thought, style and working arrangements to ensure our workforce is representative of the community that we serve.

