We are currently recruiting for a motivated and experienced Business Development Manager- Limeto support a global leader in the supply of Lime and Limestone products to service industries that include mining, construction, building product and environmental sectors. This permanent fulltime role would ideally be located within the Melbourne vicinity and would service our customers throughout Victoria.  
 Reporting to the Industry Sales Manager, this autonomous position will be responsible for developing new and  existing client relationships, and growing the business across the abovementioned sectors. The candidate will be a "hunter" and readily present technical and product information to existing and future customers.
Key responsibilities include;

Achieve sales and order volumes at the target prices within the assigned accounts/territory. 
Build relationships, plan  and develop market and customer business strategy, and maximize business opportunities for all Sibelco products & services within allocated accounts/territory.
Develop & deliver the tactical sales plan for his/her territory that successfully delivers the agreed budgeted commercial      objectives and the marketing strategy.
Provide accurate monthly sales forecasts within defined timelines.
Work collaboratively and proactively with the Sales Manager, Marketing Manager and continually develop the opportunity pipeline by seeking new customer/market opportunities/market and information on products, competitors and market trends.
Organize selling promotional activities/tactics to meet these sales and budget objectives;
Align the customer's needs and Sibelco's operational and supply chain capabilities through close cooperation with operations to      ensure optimum balance of resources and value chain;
Successfully implement the pricing policy for all products in the market stream;
Successfully utilize and apply Commercial Excellence tools and processes;

Requirements;

Proven ability to meet and exceed budgets, generate new leads to increase market share and revenue
Exceptional communication skills with a confident presentation style.Ability to synthesise and present data and trends.
Contract/Tendering experience would be an advantage.
Industrial/technical sales knowledge from the mining, construction or building product industry ideal, though not requirement.

The successful appointment must offer core desired key behaviors and cultural fit, and will be a solutions focused self-starter. This an excellent career role with ample progression opportunities in this growing company.
Applications (cover letter & CV) can be sent via the careers page on our website at www.sibelco.com/careersno later than Wednesday the 8th May 2019.
